Math.Equation

Class Function

  • java.lang.Object
    • Math.Equation.Function
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Math.MathObject
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CustomFunction, InBuiltFunction

    public abstract class Function
extends java.lang.Object
implements Math.MathObject
    A class that simulates both any kind of operation and any fuction in Math. Simply put, anything that isn't a number or variable should be a function somehow. For example, in f(x), this class would represent f.
    Since:
    0.1

      • evalNode

        protected double[] evalNode(EquationSystem pEqSys,
                            Node pNode)
        This thing takes a Node (usually the node from exec), and returns an array of the numerical values of each subNode.
        Parameters:
        pEqSys - The EquationSystem that will be used when evaluating pNode.
        pNode - The node to be evaluated.
        Returns:
        An array of doubles, with each position corresponding to the value of each Node of that position in pNode's subNodes().

      • exec

        public abstract double exec(EquationSystem pEqSys,
                            Node pNode)
                     throws NotDefinedException,
                            InvalidArgsException
        Takes the parameter Node (and EquationSystem, performs whatever this function is defined to do, and returns the result.
        Parameters:
        pEqSys - An EquationSystem that contains all relevant information about Equations and Functions is stored.
        pNode - The Node that is going to be solved.
        Returns:
        A double representing the value of pNode, when solved for with pEqSys.
        Throws:
        NotDefinedException - Thrown when the function is defined, but how to execute it isn't.
        InvalidArgsException - Thrown when the function required parameters, and the ones passed aren't right.
